there are perhaps more important people than mere politicians.

349
00:20:09,207 --> 00:20:12,324
医生 护士 急救队 等等
Doctors, nurses, ambulance men, and so on.

350
00:20:12,487 --> 00:20:14,762
从事基础服务的人
All people who run essential services.

351
00:20:14,927 --> 00:20:16,440
可是据我所知 大臣
Correct me if I'm wrong,

352
00:20:16,607 --> 00:20:19,917
首相本人和内政大臣
but is it not a fact that the PM and Home Secretary

353
00:20:20,087 --> 00:20:23,636
不也在政府掩体里留有位置吗?
have places reserved for them in government fallout shelters?

354
00:20:24,647 --> 00:20:26,683
这完全是两码事
That is completely different.

355
00:20:28,407 --> 00:20:30,204
怎讲?
How

356
00:20:30,367 --> 00:20:34,565
这个 总得有人管理...你看...
Well, there has to be someone to... run the... you know.

357
00:20:34,727 --> 00:20:37,036
大臣 您刚刚说政客
Minister, you're saying political leaders

358
00:20:37,207 --> 00:20:40,119
应该把位置让给医生护士
should give up their places for doctors and nurses.

359
00:20:40,287 --> 00:20:44,121
这个观点您向首相和内政大臣提了吗?
Have you put this idea to the PM and the Home Secretary

360
00:20:44,287 --> 00:20:47,359
我认为我们切不可把重要问题
I think we ought to be careful not to trivialise

361
00:20:47,527 --> 00:20:49,995
简单化 路德维克
what is a very serious Issue, Ludovic.

362
00:20:51,767 --> 00:20:53,439
我再举个例子
I'll give you another example.

363
00:20:53,607 --> 00:20:56,121
我刚听说 有个市的委员
I know of a borough which sent councillors,

364
00:20:56,287 --> 00:21:00,041
拿着纳税人的钱 去加州考察掩体
at the ratepayers' expensive, to California to look at shelters.

365
00:21:00,247 --> 00:21:02,442
但考察回来却无事可做
But they couldn't do anything about it

366
00:21:02,607 --> 00:21:05,360
